<P><LI> "HIV Treatment May Cost $15 Billion by 1995,"  Research Activities, U.S. Department of Health and Human 
Services, No. 155, July 1992, p. 1.
<P><LI> "HIV and Homosexuals in the Army Versus the Civilian Community," Department of the Army Information Paper, 
Office of the Deputy Chief of Staff for Personnel, January 27, 1993.
<P><LI>  "HIV Positive Analysis Report," Office of the U.S. Army Surgeon General, April 9, 1993.
<P><LI> Paul Cameron, William L. Playfair, and Stephen Wellum, "The Homosexual Lifespan,"<I> Omega</I>, Vol. 29, No. 3, 
1994, pp. 249-272.
<P><LI> Robert J. Kus, "Alcoholics Anonymous and Gay American Men,"<I> Journal of Homosexuality</I>, Vol. 14, No. 2, 1987, 
p. 254.
<P><LI> Franklin D. Jones and Ronald J. Koshes, op. cit., p. 20.
<P><LI> Ibid.
<P><LI><I> Steffan v. Perry</I>, F.2d (D.C. Cir. 1994).
<P><LI><I> Meinhold v. United States Department of Defense</I>, 1994 WL 467311 (9th Cir. Aug. 31, 1994).
<P><LI> Franklin D. Jones and Ronald J. Koshes, op. cit., p. 21.
</OL></FONT>

<p>

