Delta Kappa, 1995) 68.
<p>
<li>In the formula for first-year funding under Goals 2000, a state
is required to offer competitive subgrants to local education
agencies with 60 percent of the total state grant.  Local education
agencies must then pass on 75 percent of their monies to local
schools. See section 308(a)(1) and section 309(a)(6).
<p>
<li>Richard W. Riley, &quot;Goals 2000: Educate America Act.  Providing
a World-Class Education for Every Child,&quot;  <I>National Issues
in Education:  Goals 2000 and School-to-Work</I> 5-6.
<p>
<li>One example is:  William J. Bennett, <I>The Index of Leading
